.TH "IOT-DATA" "a" "" ""
.SH NAME
iot-data \- AWS IoT-Data enables secure, bi-directional communication between Internet-connected things (such as sensors, actuators, embedded devices, or smart appliances) and the AWS cloud
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
AWS IoT\-Data enables secure, bi\-directional communication between Internet\-connected things (such as sensors, actuators, embedded devices, or smart appliances) and the AWS cloud. It implements a broker for applications and things to publish messages over HTTP (Publish) and retrieve, update, and delete shadows. A shadow is a persistent representation of your things and their state in the AWS cloud.
.sp
Find the endpoint address for actions in the AWS IoT data plane by running this CLI command:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
\fBaws iot describe\-endpoint \-\-endpoint\-type iot:Data\-ATS\fP
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
The service name used by \fI\%AWS Signature Version 4\fP to sign requests is: \fIiotdevicegateway\fP .
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The default endpoint data.iot.[region].amazonaws.com is intended for testing purposes only. For production code it is strongly recommended to use the custom endpoint for your account  (retrievable via the iot describe\-endpoint command) to ensure best availability and reachability of the service.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
